Better than candy!! 🍫🍫🍫
So easy, and just one or two is all you need to curb your sweet tooth. Have you ever tried these?!

How To:

-Cut in half and remove seeds of big medjool dates - set aside.

-Heat up your favorite dark chocolate combined with a tiny spoonful of coconut oil- this makes it extra drippy. Stir until melted and let cool slightly. 

-Fill your dates up with peanut butter, or almond butter (tahini would be good too!) and place on parchment paper. 

-Last step- drizzle your chocolate over the dates. As much or as little as you want. 

Put in freezer for at least one hour before transferring to the fridge. 
Enjoy as dessert or a snack!

BIRTH STORY! 

birth is long, intense, gnarly, and the hardest thing I’ve ever done. No matter if you had complications or not, birth is HARD. Mamas you’re amazing. 

It’s Tuesday and I’m at my 39 week appointment. My Doctor checks my cervix. I’m 1cm. I ask her to do a stretch and sweep. She gets me to 2cm. Meanwhile I am repeatedly getting high blood pressure readings. She takes one final reading and says I’m sending you to the hospital just to be safe, you could be able to go home, we’ll see. I also give a pee sample and a blood draw. At this point I really think I’m going to get to go home from the hospital and I’m actually happy bc I’m 2cm! 

We get to labor and delivery- my blood pressure is still high. They put in a hep lock to be ready for an IV drip. The nurses tell me I’m likely not going home. My urine and blood come back and suddenly I’m told I have severe pre eclampsia, I’m at risk for seizure and they need to get this baby out now. They want to start to induce me ASAP. 

At this point, I’m panicking. I start crying, asking “what did I do wrong?” Nothing they say, this is random and there is no rhyme or reason for it. My placenta is no longer working for my body and the only way to “cure” pre eclampsia is to deliver the baby. My husband and I have a short cry with our doula and then we buckle up and say let’s do this. This is our path we have to move forward. 

They put me on a sulfate magnesium drip to prevent seizure. I have a constant blood pressure cuff on going off every 30 min. I also have two monitors for baby. The ONLY thing keeping me going is knowing that the baby is perfectly healthy and fine. Her heart rate did not dip once through my entire labor and she was happy the whole time. It was not the baby in danger, it was me. 

We started the induction pills Cytotec around noon. This kick started contractions. Though they were very light, it felt like slightly annoying period pain. I knew the pitocin was coming…
They decided to start me on pitocin at 11pm. I knew I was in for a gnarly night. In my mind I still wanted to try for a natural birth but I also knew that the pitocin was about to hit me like a train…

Healthy Banana Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Cookies 🍪 🍌 

Here’s my super easyyy 1 bowl recipe, combine: 
3 brown mashed bananas
2 TBSP nut or seed butter (I used tahini for a more subtle flavor)
1 egg
1 1/2 cups instant oats
1/2 cup gluten free flour
Pinch of sea salt
1/2 cup chocolate chips (heaping 1/2 cup)

Use a cookie scoop to make 1/2 inch balls on a lined baking tray. Bake at 350 for 12 min!

For my sweet tooth people who need a healthier option…you’re welcome! Also great for breast feeding mamas (oats help milk production)
.

My best ever and EASY Chicken Noodle Soup Recipe:
What you need- can add more or less to make a bigger batch. I often freeze a couple jars. 

1 onion chopped 
2-3 large carrots chopped
2-3 large celery stalks chopped
2 garlic cloves smashed 
1-2 tbsp fresh grated ginger 
3-4 red or gold potatoes quartered
Salt
Pepper 
Sauté all the above in a big Dutch oven type of pot with a generous amount of olive oil.
Once onions are nice and translucent add:
4 cups chicken stock
2 large chicken breasts 
Cook with lid for 20-30 min. Remove chicken and shred with two forks. Put shredded chicken back in pot. Simmer all day long. About 30 min before serving add your noodles and Dino kale (about 4-5 leaves chopped). I’ve been using gluten free buckwheat noodles but any work!

Serve with toasted sourdough, or our favorite in this household, grilled cheese. 
Enjoy 🍲 🍞 
.
